cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CY 

This paper focuses on the task of extracting coordinate terms in Chinese from web search results, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses a semi-supervised method that integrates manually defined linguistic patterns and automatically learned semi-structural patterns, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques for grouping terms into different concepts and calculating saliency scores, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Learning). Finally, the paper deals with Chinese language processing, which is a sub-field of cs.CY (Computational Linguistics).
